      <p>Value investing involves finding companies that appear to be trading for less than their intrinsic or book value. These are often mature businesses that have temporarily fallen out of favor with the broader market due to short-term headwinds or sector-wide pessimism. The astute investor recognizes these dislocations and capitalizes on the discrepancy between price and fundamental value, anticipating an eventual reversion to the mean.</p>

